Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit 1353 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA Unit 1353. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After receiving a salute from commanding officers of the unit on the spot, he dropped in at the military lecture room to acquaint himself with the training of its servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks to be fulfilled by the unit to further increase its combat capability, expressing satisfaction over the fact that its servicepersons are undergoing intensive training to prepare themselves as a-match-for-a hundred fighters possessed of a high level of military technique and combat capability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unit could make this shining success because it used its brain and made indefatigable efforts to effectively carry out its programme for training, he said, adding that the primary revolutionary task of the soldiers is to train themselves well. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He learned in detail about its soldiers' service and living, making the rounds of an education room, bedroom, mess hall, wash-cum-bath house, barber's, non-staple food store and other places. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After seeing the interior and the compound of the barracks, he expressed great satisfaction over the fact that the unit has successfully built up entertainment, educational and supply service facilities to the convenience of its soldiers' living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was pleased to see all the servicepersons of the unit making every moment of their military service worthwhile with intense loyalty to the party and the revolution and sent them congratulations on their military feats. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Informed of Pak Kyong Sik, non-commissioned officer in extra service, who has made a great contribution to improving the supply service, serving at the unit for more than 3 decades, Kim Jong Il called him an ardent revolutionary who has worked heart and soul at the post for defending the country for years and highly praised his patriotic devotion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
He underscored the need for all units to actively develop the sideline economy to provide the soldiers with better living conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su.

Kim Jong Il Inspects KPA Unit 1366 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il inspected KPA Unit 1366. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After learning about the unit's performance of duty, he looked round the apparatuses contrived and manufactured by it on its own. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is gratifying that the unit manufactured various apparatuses helpful to increasing the combat capability by enlisting the wisdom and creative ingenuity of the commanding officers and men and are making a good use of them, he noted, highly appreciating the revolutionary spirit of self-reliance displayed by the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was pleased to learn that the servicepersons of the unit are well versed in combat and technical equipment and prizing and handling weapons of the revolution like the apples of their eyes and creditably carrying out their tasks, firmly determined to defend the happiness of the people and the man-centred socialist system in the DPRK at the cost of their lives. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 While making the rounds of an education room, bedroom, mess hall, wash-cum-bath house, daily provision store and other entertainment, educational and supply service facilities, he paid deep attention to the service and living of the servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He highly appreciated the habit of reading prevalent in the unit, saying that only when one reads many books can one deeply grasp the Party line and policies and acquire wide-ranging and profound knowledge about politics, economy and culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He praised the unit for having provided the soldiers with good living conditions by assiduously managing the economic life, underscoring the need for the commanding officers to always pay deep attention to the supply service, well aware of its importance, and thus provide them with the best living conditions as they are devoting themselves to protecting the security of the country and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Seeing the imposing appearance of the unit's servicepersons, he said that voluntary and steel-strong discipline is the essential characteristics of a revolutionary army and a sure guarantee for boosting combat capability. He called for making sustained efforts to thoroughly establish revolutionary military discipline. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He had a photo session with the servicepersons of the unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He was accompanied by KPA Generals Hyon Chol Hae and Ri Myong Su.

Grand Gymnastic and Artistic Performance "Arirang" Given 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The grand gymnastic and artistic  performance "Arirang", the winner of "Kim Il Sung Prize", was staged at the May Day Stadium in Pyongyang today as the first presentation in the year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "Arirang" was created and completed and staged, drawing capacity spectators on the occasion of the 90th birth anniversary of President Kim Il Sung. It is a monumental masterpiece in the new century as it evoked admiration among the world people for its profound ideological contents and high level of artistry, peculiar style, vast scale, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The creating group and performers succeeded in splendidly re-representing the extravaganza in a brief span of time. They newly created Scene 5 of Chapter 2 "Silk Producing Girls in Nyongbyon" and depicted in a peculiar manner the inexhaustible mental power and skills of the Korean people in various chapters and scenes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When the merry melody of the song "Pyongyang Is Best" resounded forth at the stadium, letters "Highest Tribute to the Great Leader, the Founding Father of the Country", "Highest Glory to the Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il" and other letters flashed across the background of the stadium one after another and its floor turned into a veritable sea of flower-waving performers. The performance began amid this jubilation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers presented three-dimensional fascinating extravaganza, a good combination of elegant music and dances, dynamic mass gymnastic movements, super-large screens, the ever-changing background of the stadium, splendid electronic displays, laser lightning, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was enjoyed by Kwak Pom Gi, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Kang Nung Su, minister of Culture, Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, leading officials of working people's organizations, working people in Pyongyang and from local areas, overseas compatriots and foreign guests.

Torrential Rains Hit DPRK 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Heavy rains poured in many parts of the DPRK from August one to three, influenced by the low pressure created in the middle of the West Sea of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The precipitations in Sepho, Hoeyang, Kosong and Phyonggang areas of Kangwon Province and Paechon and Yonan areas of South Hwanghae Province were respectively 322mm, 303mm, 244mm, 225mm, 224mm and 177mm on August two alone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Kumgang and Sepho areas of Kangwon Province and Songchon area of South Phyongan Province experienced downpours of 127mm, 120mm and 108mm respectively in 00:00-03:00, 12:00-15:00 and 15:00-18:00 on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In particular it rained in torrents in Kumgang County for 9 hours. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the three days rainfalls of over 150-300 mm were observed in areas of Kangwon, North and South Phyongan and South Hwanghae provinces and rainfalls of more than 50mm in over 10 cities and counties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It rained heavily in most parts of the DPRK on July 20, 21, 24 and 25. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The recent downpours inflicted heavy losses to various sectors of the national economy including agriculture and to the people's living in the relevant areas.

Kim Yong Nam Meets CILRECO Secretary General 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, met and had a talk in a cordial atmosphere with Guy Dupre, secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, and his family at the Mansudae Assembly Hall on Monday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand was Kim Thae Jong, vice department director of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Family of Guy Dupre 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the family of Guy Dupre, secretary general of the International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea, on a visit to the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People�fs Assembly, by Guy Dupre on Monday.

Greetings to PM of Jamaica 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Premier of the DPRK Cabinet Kim Yong Il sent a message of greetings to Jamaican Prime Minister Bruce Golding on August 1 on the occasion of the 46th anniversary of the independence of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message wished him success in the work for the prosperity of the country and welfare of its people.

"World Breastfeeding Week" Observed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- An event took place at the People's Palace of Culture today on the occasion of the "World Breastfeeding Week." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the event were officials concerned and health officials in Pyongyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of missions of international organizations including the UNICEF here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Pong Hun, vice-minister of Public Health, made an opening address at the event to be followed by speeches of Gopalan Balagopal, representative of the UNICEF, and Arvind Mathur, acting representative of the WHO. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They referred to the fact that the UNICEF set the period from August 1 to 7 every year as the "World Breastfeeding Week" and recommended all countries to conduct various activities related to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lecture on mother's lactation was given. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants looked round the posters on the week before enjoying a performance given by a group for hygienic information service.

Jonsung Revolutionary Museum Renewed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The Jonsung Revolutionary Museum has been wonderfully renewed as a centre for ideological education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its officials and employees erected a mosaic carrying a picture of President Kim Il Sung, the invincible and iron-willed commander who led the Fatherland Liberation War to victory, rebuilt and repaired the exhibition rooms and displayed materials and relics anew. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also renewed the system and form of exhibiting relics and data to help visitors get a better understanding of the immortal feats of the President who led the war to victory by arousing the whole party and army and all the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many additional materials and data have been displayed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among them are historic photographs, including those titled "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung makes an address before the teachers and students of Kim Il Sung University" and "The great leader Comrade Kim Il Sung poses for a picture with Comrade Kim Chaek", and fine art works carrying the image of the President, including "For independence, freedom and honor of the country!", a poster produced during the Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is also multimedia which carries the venerable image and voice of the President making a speech at the Pyongyang mass rally held on July 28, Juche 42 (1953) to celebrate the victory in the Fatherland Liberation War. This enriches the contents of revolutionary relics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Exhibited at the museum are such famous works of the President as "Let Us Wipe Out the Invaders by a Decisive Counter-Offensive" and "Go All Out for Victory in the War". Displayed at exhibition rooms are his important teachings and the Workers' Party of Korea's militant slogans set forth during the war in conformity with the contents of the exhibition rooms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  On display there are also such documents as decisions of the DPRK Military Commission and the Cabinet and a message of thanks the President sent to the farmers who reaped a good harvest and tens of photos and newspapers introducing the heroic fighting spirit and indomitable stamina displayed by the Korean army and people in the front and rear under the leadership of the party and the leader. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibits include posters created in the days of war and materials and data showing the state benefits for war sufferers, the preparations of universal free medical care system and the innovative achievements made in the wartime production and transport.

Mt. Paekun Pleasure Ground
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The Mt. Paekun Pleasure Ground in Yonggwang County, South Hamgyong Province is a favorite place of working people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The scenery of Mt. Paekun covered with fir and other trees and abundant wild fruits, edible and medicinal herbs gives deep emotion to the visitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Conspicuous are the Sanju Falls, Tongdae Falls and Manjang Falls from which crystal-clear water rolls down, sharp rock-peaks, deep valleys and quaint rocks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is a specifically built pavilion in the mid-slope of the mountain which well harmonizes with the thickly-wooded surrounding scenery. From it the holiday-makers have a good time, commanding a bird's-eye view of mountains and streams, which spread a fascinating beauty along with clouds wrapping the waists of mountains. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The well-furnished peasants' rest home built in a thick forest provides the holiday-makers with good rest conditions and colorful cultural and emotional life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is in the mountain the Ryonghung Temple (1048), a historical and cultural relic belonging to Koryo.

Green Woods on Rough Sea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Scenic green woods are spreading along the large-sized, long-distance belt conveyor of the Unryul Mine on the west coast of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The woods have taken shape on the scraped earth carried by the gigantic belt conveyor built in the 1970s over the last 30 years or more. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The officials and workers of the mine have planted lots of trees along the belt conveyor stretching farther into the sea for decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several dozen hectares of woods have extended from Kumsan Bay to Nunggum Islet and then to Ung Islet and now, changing its course, is stretching from Nunggum Islet to Jwi Islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Growing there are more than 1.2 million trees of 12 species such fruit trees as persimmon, apricot and sweet cherry trees and clammy locust and golden-bell flower trees. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A road runs parallel to the belt conveyor through the woods. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Birds and beasts have built their nests in the thick woods where flowers come in bloom in spring and summer and various fruits ripen in autumn. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the observation platform of the mine one can enjoy a panoramic view of the scenic wonders of the woods stretching into the sea along the long-distance belt conveyor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many working people, school youths and children are coming to the woods to spend their holidays.

Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Work Observed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- "Let Us Carry Out the Great Leader Comrade Kim Il Sung's Instructions for National Reunification", a work of General Secretary Kim Jong Il, serves as an undying library which clearly indicates the way to be followed by the Korean nation's movement for national reunification and a militant banner which dynamically promotes the advance of the June 15 era of reunification, says Rodong Sinmun Monday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work comprehensively deals with the immortal feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in the cause of national reunification and clearly indicates the tasks to be fulfilled to settle the issue of the country's reunification on the principle of national independence and great unity in accordance with his intention and behest and the ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a great historic feat performed by Kim Jong Il that he in the work formulated the three principles of national reunification, the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo advanced by the President as the three charters for national reunification and provided a militant banner which powerfully arouses all the fellow countrymen to the drive to carry out his instructions for reunification, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic events that have taken place for the past 11 years since the publication of the work and remarkable achievements made in the struggle for national reconciliation and unity and the independent and peaceful reunification of the country in this period are a clear proof of the attraction and vitality of the work. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The key to achieving the reunification of the country and exalting the dignity and honor of the nation is to invariably uphold the idea, line and policy of the President for national reunification as a banner in the June 15 era of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the basic way of settling the issue of the country's reunification at an early date in line with the will and interests of the Korean nation to carry out the cause of national reunification independently on the principle of national independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historic June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration, a programme for its implementation, serve as great programmes for achieving independent national reunification as they correctly reflect the Juche-based idea and line of the President for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of "By our nation itself" is the basic spirit of these declarations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When all the fellow countrymen are united close under the banner of great national unity, they can overcome any difficulties and certainly achieve the cause of national reunification.

Campaign for Boycotting American Beef Declared in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The People's Measure Council against the Total Opening of south Korean Market to American Beef called a press conference in Seoul on August 1 to declare a campaign for boycotting American beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization disclosed that according to the quarantine standard announced by the U.S. Department of Agriculture on July 20, X-rays is to be used for sterilizing beef. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After all the south Korean people may suffer damage by not only mad cow disease but also X-rays, the organization pointed out, declaring that it would launch the above-said campaign to protect the people's right to health.

Action of Pomchonghakryon Reunification Vanguard Started in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The 21st-term Reunification Vanguard of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) on August 1 started its action to stage a grand candlelight march for sovereignty and peace against war and conduct a struggle demanding renegotiations on American beef import and punishment of Lee Myung Bak and opposing Bush's trip to south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jong Tok Won, chief of the vanguard, made an address at the ceremony of starting its action held in front of the U.S. embassy in Seoul on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the vanguard would be organized around August 15 this year, too, to stir up the atmosphere of reunification across south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organization will conduct its activities in real earnest with Bush's trip to south Korea as an occasion, he noted, adding: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It will vigorously wage information activities and struggle for peace against war in Seoul, Inchon and Kyonggi Province till August 7, holding high the slogans "Renegotiations on American beef import!" and "Opposition to Bush's trip to south Korea!" &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After that it will stage an all-people grand candlelight march to punish the Lee Myung Bak "government" and retake the lost sovereignty, touring all parts of south Korea, divided into the east and west groups. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is as clear as noonday that Lee Myung Bak's days will be numbered if he disregards and cracks down upon the people as the military dictators in the past did, the chief said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Letters of protest to traitor Lee Myung Bak and Bush were read out at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letters urged Lee to stop tightening the "alliance" for aggression with the United States, implement the June 15 joint declaration and the October 4 declaration and the United States to come out to the total renegotiations on beef import as soon as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the ceremony the vanguard conducted information activities in different parts of Seoul.

Scheme to Put Media under "Gov't" Control Slashed in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- A candlelight rally took place outside the KBS Office of south Korea on August 1 to accuse traitor Lee Myung Bak of his scheme to put broadcasting stations under the "government" control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Attending it were members of the all-people action against the scheme to control broadcasting stations and suppression of netizens and citizens, over 500 in all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They charged that the Lee Myung Bak group is getting evermore pronounced in the moves to control public broadcasting services while seeking to suppress netizens with a new count called "cyber insult".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They demanded an immediate stop to such action of going against the times.

Lee Myung Bak Regime's Submissive Diplomacy Blasted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- The South Side Headquarters of the National Alliance for the Country's Reunification issued a statement on July 30 flaying the Lee Myung Bak regime's submissive diplomacy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement deplored the fact that Japan recently announced that it would write Tok Islet as part of the Japanese territory in the "new teaching guidelines" for the social subjects of primary and middle schools of Japan and in its wake the U.S. Board on Geographic Names marked the islet as an area of undesignated sovereignty. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This deplorable development was the tragic result of the submissive diplomacy pursued by the Lee Myung Bak "government", the statement noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Lee is encouraging Japan in its moves to revive militarism, talking about "future-oriented development of relations, without asking about its past" though it is seized with its wild ambition to grab other's territory. Moreover, Lee is begging the U.S. for "closer alliance" though it pressurized south Korea to import beef from cattle infected with mad cow disease. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The sycophantic diplomacy pursued by the group of traitors in subservience to the policies of aggression of the U.S. and Japan while talking about "friendship" and "alliance" resulted in infringing upon the right to quarantine, the territorial sovereignty and the right to existence on this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people condemn the Lee "government" for kowtowing to the U.S., taking a foolish attitude towards Japan and following a perfidious policy towards the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Lee "government" continues yielding to the U.S. and Japan, it will face all-people resistance, warned the statement.

Day of Korean People's Victory in War Celebrated Abroad
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Meetings, book and photo exhibitions and film shows were held in Britain and Laos on July 23 and 28 to mark the 55th anniversary of the Korean people's victory in the great Fatherland Liberation War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venues of the functions were photographs showing the Songun leadership feats of the peerlessly great men and books and photos introducing the popular heroism and undaunted struggle of the Korean army and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meetings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Harpal Brar, chairman of the C.C., the Communist Party of Great Britain (Marxist-Leninist), Michael Chant, secretary of the C.C., the Revolutionary Communist Party of Britain (Marxist-Leninist), Dermot Hudson, chairman of the British Association for the Study of Songun Policy, and Keith Bennet, deputy director-general of the European Society for the Study of the Juche Idea, elaborated on the immortal feats performed by President Kim Il Sung in leading the Fatherland Liberation War to victory and the admirable achievements made by the Korean army and people in socialist construction under the Songun revolutionary leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They called for further strengthening support and solidarity with the Korean people who have firmly defended socialism despite the imperialists' moves to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The manager of the Laos-Korea Tin Company said it was a noteworthy event in the world history of wars that the DPRK won victory in the hard-fought war of three years against the U.S. imperialists who boasted of being "the strongest" in the world. The Korean people's shining victory in the war was thanks to the outstanding leadership of Kim Il Sung, the invincible and iron-willed commander, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting held in Britain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Appreciated at the film shows were Korean films showing the invincible might of the heroic Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Saber Ballul, head of a department of the Political Faculty of the University of Damascus, issued a statement on July 25 to celebrate July 27, the day of the Korean people's victory in the war.

Three Charters for Korea's Reunification Supported
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, August 4 (KCNA) -- Personages of Indonesia and Thailand issued statements in support of the three charters for Korea's reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Indonesian Maritime Transport Workers Union in a statement on July 26 recalled that General Secretary Kim Jong Il formulated the three principles of national reunification, the 10-point programme of the great unity of the whole nation and the proposal for founding the Democratic Federal Republic of Koryo as the three charters for national reunification on August 4, 1997. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said it was thanks to the three charters that the June 15 North-South Joint Declaration was adopted eight years ago, greatly contributing to relaxing the tension on the Korean Peninsula and opening up a new era of reconciliation and cooperation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He declared that they would always extend full support to the Korean people in the just struggle to achieve the independent and peaceful reunification of the country in the basic spirit of the three charters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A former lawmaker of Thailand in a statement on July 30 praised the three charters as the guidelines that should be held fast to by all the Koreans aspiring after the national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the most fair and reasonable programme for Korea's reunification, the three charters has enjoyed the unanimous support of all the Koreans, he added.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona la subunidad de unidad naval No. 155 EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 4 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente   Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea (EPC), inspecciono una subunidad adscrita a la Unidad No. 155 de las Fuerzas Navales del EPC laureada con el Titulo del Septimo Regimiento de O Jung Hup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Despues de recibir el saludo mediante la guardia de honor el Dirigente Kim Jong Il recorrio el historico buque de guerra en que el Presidente Kim Il Sung dio el 24 de mayo de 1970 las preciosas ensenanzas para el desarrollo de las fuerzas navales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recordar con gran emocion ese inolvidable dia historico elogio  que hicieron bien la conservacion y la administracion del buque impregnado de las hazanas directivas del Presidente y dijo que brillaran eternamente en los anales de la patria las inmortales hazanas revolucionarias del Presidente acumuladas en la construccion  autoctona de las fuerzas navales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En la sala de mando operacional se entero del estado de cumplimiento de guardia avanzada y de ejercicios de la Unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se  mostro satisfecho de que todos los militares de la unidad cumplen con alta vigilancia el deber combativo observando agudamente todos los movimientos de los enemigos y que todos los oficiales disponen de la elevada tecnica de empleo del buque y la capacidad de mando y presento las tareas que se presentan en fortalecer por todos los medios la combatividad de la unidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al recorrer las instalaciones de cultura, educacion e intendencia de la unidad presto una profunda atencion a la vida de los marineros&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Estuvo  contento de que los oficiales de la unidad aseguraron bien las condiciones de vida comoda a los marineros y elogio sus esfuerzos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Departio cordialmente con Choe Jong Su quien trabaja de capitan del buque en esa subunidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El Dirigente se fotografio junto a los militares de la subunidad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le acompanaron los generales de ejercito del EPC Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su.

Kim Jong Il presencia la funcion del grupo artistico de la Unidad No. 757
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 4 de agosto (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, presencio la funcion del grupo de propaganda artistica de la Unidad No.757 del EPC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Los ejecutantes pusieron en la escena diversas piezas de distintas formas entre otras la agitacion en dialogo "El General se encuentra en el campo de entrenamiento", el trio femenino "Los soldados cantan nuestro Comandante Supremo", la agitacion dramatica "Los ojos linces", el cuarteto masculino "Esta conocido a todo el pais", el solo masculino "Patria que defiendo" y la poesia a coro "Agarraremos mas fuertemente el fusil y la espada de aniquilamiento a los enemigos".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
El Comandante Supremo se mostro muy satisfecho de que los miembros del grupo de propaganda artistica de la unidad crearon las excelentes obras que reflejan fielmente la infinita mentalidad de nuestros militares y ofrecieron una funcion veridica y combativa y evaluo altamente el exito de la funcion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Dijo que es importantisima la propaganda artistica de gran poder influyente y exhortativo en la educacion ideologica para los militares y presento las tareas programaticas que sirven de guia para fortalecer mas actividades de propaganda artistica revolucionarias y combativas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Lo vieron tambien los generales de ejercito del EPC Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su y otros miembros directivos del ejercito,  el jefe de departamento del CC del PTC Jang Song Thaek y los primeros subjefes de departamentos del CC del PTC Ri Yong Chol y Ri Je Gang y otros cuadros directivos del CC del PTC.

Cayo lluvia torrencial en Corea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 4 de agosto (ATCC) -- A consecuencia de la depresion atmosferica originada en la parte central del Mar Oeste de Corea, la mayoria de la extension geografica del pais fue sorprendida por las lluvias torrenciales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante el dia 2, las precipitaciones reportadas en Sepho, Hoeyang, Kosong y Phyonggang de la provincia de Kangwon y las regiones de Paechon y Yonan de la provincia de Hwanghae del Sur fueron 322, 303, 244, 225, 224 y 177 milimetros, respectivamente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas, en los horarios 0-3, 12-15 y 15-18 de ese dia cayeron 127, 120 y 108 milimetros en Kumgang y Sepho de la provincia de Kangwon y la region de Songchon de la provincia de Phyong-an del Sur. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En particular, el aguacero persistio 9 horas en el distrito de Kumgang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante los primeros 3 dias del mes en curso, las aguas pluviales marcaron 150-300 mm o mas en las provincias de Kangwon, Phyong-an del Sur y del Norte y Hwanghae del Sur y mas de 50 mm en mas de 10 ciudades y distritos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Habia sucedido igual fenomeno los dias 20, 21, 24 y 25 de julio. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El nuevo azote de la lluvia torrencial ocasiono considerables danos en varios sectores de la economia nacional, en particular, la agricultura y la vida popular de las regiones afectadas.
